            <h1>Layering for Cold Weather</h1>
            <p>Live in a cold climate, work outdoors, play cold-weather sports or recently moved somewhere more frigid than you&rsquo;re used to? Then it&rsquo;s important to learn the basics of layering for cold weather.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="large-9 small-10 large-centered small-centered column">
            <h2>How To Add Layers For Cold Weather?</h2>
            <p>The key to staying warm in very cold conditions is by layering clothes instead of wearing one layer of thick, heavy items. Macy&rsquo;s has everything you need to create the warmest (and most stylish) outfits you can dream up.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row ce-mobile-full ce-mobile-collapse">
        <div class="large-11 small-12 large-centered column">
            <img class="ceg-b32" src="//assets.macysassets.com/dyn_img/creativepages/Q8060009-105-02.jpg" alt="Start with a thermal base layer">
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row ceg-t35">
        <div class="large-9 small-10 large-centered small-centered column">
            <h5>1. START WITH A THERMAL BASE LAYER.</h5>
            <p class="ceg-b32">
                It&rsquo;s important to build a solid foundation if you plan to stay warm this winter. A thermal base layer should be worn closest to your skin. Make sure it&rsquo;s quick-drying, retains heat and is comfortable. Brands like 32 Degrees, Polo Ralph Lauren, 2(X)IST and Alfani (created for Macy&rsquo;s) have solid options in various designs and colors. Here are a few options to get you started:
            </p>
            <ul class="bullet-list">
                <li><strong>Thermal Underwear.</strong> Whether <a href="{{ENV_HOSTNAME}}/shop/b/mens-thermal-underwear?id=72557">thermal underwear</a> or long johns, allow men&rsquo;s thermals including be your first layer of protection.</li>
                <li><strong>Thermal Undershirts.</strong> A full-coverage undershirt will provide all-day comfort. Stock up on crewnecks, mock necks and henleys in a moisture-wicking fabric or a warm waffle weave.</li>
                <li><strong>Thermal Leggings.</strong> Thin fabric with lots of stretch is key when it comes to thermal leggings. They should fit seamlessly underneath your pants and allow you to be flexible.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row ce-mobile-full ce-mobile-collapse">
        <div class="large-11 small-12 large-centered column">
            <img class="ceg-b32" src="//assets.macysassets.com/dyn_img/creativepages/Q8060009-105-03.jpg" alt="Add a sweater">
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row ceg-t35">
        <div class="large-9 small-10 large-centered small-centered column">
            <h5>2. ADD A SWEATER.</h5>
            <p class="ceg-b32">
                Now that you&rsquo;ve got momentum with a base layer, keep it going by adding a thin, lightweight <a href="{{ENV_HOSTNAME}}/shop/mens-clothing/mens-sweaters?id=4286">sweater</a> in any of these crowd-pleasing styles:
            </p>
            <ul class="bullet-list">
                <li><strong>Crewneck.</strong> A classic for a reason, a simple <a href="{{ENV_HOSTNAME}}/shop/mens-clothing/mens-sweaters/Sweater_style/Crew%20Neck?id=4286">crewneck sweater</a> works well with both casual and dressed-up outfits. Take your pick of timeless and trendy colors.</li>
                <li><strong>V-Neck.</strong> A super-versatile sweater you&rsquo;ll reach for again and again. The trick is to layer the <a href="{{ENV_HOSTNAME}}/shop/b/mens-v-neck-sweaters?id=72218">V-neck</a> over a polished button-up shirt or simple T-shirt.</li>
                <li><strong>Turtleneck.</strong> Who needs a scarf when your sweater will keep your neck warm? Men&rsquo;s turtlenecks are having a moment and they look great with almost everything from jeans to trousers.</li>
                <li><strong>Quarter Zip.</strong> The simple pullover has gone modern. This athletic-inspired style is elevated thanks to discreet zippers, fresh fabrics and a tailored fit.</li>
                <li><strong>Full Zip.</strong> The <a href="{{ENV_HOSTNAME}}/shop/mens-clothing/mens-sweaters/Sweater_style/Full%20Zip?id=4286">full-zip sweater</a> can be worn a couple different ways&ndash;rock it fully zipped as a sweater or unzipped as a jacket. It&rsquo;s also the perfect backdrop to showcase your personal style through mixed media, prints and colorblocking.</li>
                <li><strong>Hoodie.</strong> The ultimate laid-back option, a <a href="{{ENV_HOSTNAME}}/shop/mens-clothing/hoodies-for-men/Sweater_style/Hoodie?id=25995">hoodie</a> is great for casual days. Modern versions actually go beyond sportswear thanks to their sleek tailoring and neutral colors.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

