    <div class="row ceg-t35">
        <div class="large-9 small-10 large-centered small-centered column">
            <h5>3. PICK THE RIGHT FABRICS.</h5>
            <p class="ceg-b32">
                Your top layer should be made of a fabric that will keep you toasty and look stylish. Here are a few cold-weather favorites to keep on your radar:
            </p>
            <ul class="bullet-list">
                <li><strong>Cashmere.</strong> This luxurious fabric is ultra soft and lightweight but still warm. It&rsquo;s used in a variety of sweater styles including crew neck and V-neck. It&rsquo;s ideal for layering underneath a heavy winter coat or jacket. Club Room (Created for Macy&rsquo;s) specializes in cashmere that&rsquo;s perfect for cold-weather layering. How to wash cashmere? Always follow the tag&rsquo;s instructions, but typically, it&rsquo;s best to avoid machine washing or drying cashmere. Instead, handwash cashmere using a mild soap and lukewarm water.</li>
                <li><strong>Merino Wool.</strong> Fine, soft, washable and easy to care for, we carry beautiful merino wool sweaters from Calvin Klein, Club Room (Created for Macy&rsquo;s), Tasso Elba (Created for Macy&rsquo;s) and more. Often seen in pullover sweaters with various necklines such as crew neck, V-neck, quarter zip and full zip. How to wash wool? Follow the care instructions on the garment tag.</li>
                <li><strong>Moisturize-Wicking.</strong> Sweat still happens in cold temperatures, so it&rsquo;s important to make sure the layer that&rsquo;s closest to your skin has moisture-wicking properties. It&rsquo;s a great way to ensure you stay warm and dry.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row ce-mobile-full ce-mobile-collapse">
        <div class="large-11 small-12 large-centered column">
            <img class="ceg-b32" src="//assets.macysassets.com/dyn_img/creativepages/Q8060009-105-05.jpg" alt="Keep your feet insulated">
